You can use `components(separatedBy:)` instance method of String to get an array containing substrings from the receiver that have been divided by a given separator. From the resultant array&#39;s count you could get the occurrences of separator in the given string. In your case as you need to get the occurrences of each element in your names array, your code would end up something like the one below.

```
var namesOccurences: [String:Int] = [:]
for chapter in genesis!.chapters{
    for verse in chapter.verses{
        for verse in verses {
            for name in names {
                let occurences = verse.value.components(separatedBy: name).count - 1
                namesOccurences[name] = namesOccurences[name, default: 0] + occurences
            }
        }
    }
}
``` 

The above method will find words that the names are substrings of as well. If you don&#39;t want that to be counted, you can split the verse into words and then loop through them to find the occurrences. Sample code would be like the one follows.

```
var namesOccurences: [String:Int] = [:]
