I&#39;ve been struggling with an issue. I need to include an id to HTTP header for filtering back-end data. The id is must be taken from a store. It&#39;s expected to be an user select an option on a site. According to the option, id will save to the store, and all following requests to a server will include the id.

I tried to make 2 sequences from given request and the store, using switchMap operator, but my HttpInterceptor didn&#39;t work. Any requests from application don&#39;t send to a server, although, the code in request$ variable works as it&#39; expected.

**UPDATE**
I&#39;ve solved the issue. The problem was linked with the store. My store had to got values from backend, but some rows in the code banned the first request to the backend for getting needed values. The solution below.

```typescript
// this code doesn&#39;t work as it&#39;s expected
export class ExtraDataInterceptor implements HttpInterceptor {

  constructor(private store: Store&lt;fromRoot.AppState&gt;) { }

  intercept(request: HttpRequest&lt;any&gt;, next: HttpHandler): Observable&lt;HttpEvent&lt;any&gt;&gt; {

    const vpo$ = this.store
      .pipe(
        select(fromRoot.selectVpoState()),
        map((state: any) =&gt; getSelected(state))
      );

    const request$ = of(request);
  
    
    return request$
      .pipe(
        map( d =&gt; {
          return combineLatest([of(d), vpo$]);
        }),
        mergeAll(),
        filter( (d: any) =&gt; d[1]), // only not empty values
        switchMap( (d: any) =&gt; {
          let r = d[0];
          const vpo = d[1];
          r = r.clone({setHeaders: {&#39;id-vpo&#39;: `${vpo.id}`}});
          return next.handle(r);
        })       
      );
  }
}

// SOLUTION
intercept(request: HttpRequest&lt;any&gt;, next: HttpHandler): Observable&lt;HttpEvent&lt;any&gt;&gt; {

    const vpo$ = this.store
      .pipe(
        select(fromRoot.selectVpoState()),
        map((state: any) =&gt; getSelected(state))
      );

    return vpo$
      .pipe(
        map( vpo =&gt; (vpo ? vpo.id : null)),
        first( id =&gt; id !== null || request.url.indexOf(&#39;vpo_active&#39;) !== -1),
        map( id =&gt; ( id ?  request.clone({setHeaders: {&#39;id-vpo&#39;: `${id}`}}) :  request)),
        switchMap( cloneRequest =&gt; next.handle(cloneRequest)),
        catchError((error: HttpErrorResponse) =&gt; {
          return throwError(error);
        })
      );
  }

